message: "If you reference this guide, please cite it as below."
title: "How Do You Know Your AI Agent Actually Works?"
abstract: >-
  A free short book on AI agent evaluation. It follows one developer from a
  production failure that 340 passing tests could not predict, through building
  an evaluation set, writing rubrics, choosing between code judges, human judges
  and AI judges, and finally running an agent in production where the evaluation
  set is grown by production itself. Part of the Harness Engineering Series.
